title:Creamy Turkey Soup
ingredients:1 large onion, chopped//
3 celery ribs, sliced//
6 tablespoons butter//
6 tablespoons flour//
1 teaspoon salt//
1/4 teaspoon pepper//
1/4 teaspoon garlic powder//
1/2 teaspoon thyme//
1/2 teaspoon savory flakes//
1/2 teaspoon parsley flakes//
1 1/2 cups milk//
4 cups cubed cooked turkey//
5 medium carrots, sliced//
1 to 2 cups turkey or chicken broth//
1 package (10 ounce) frozen peas
instructions:In a large kettle, saute onion and celery in butter till tender.//
Stir in flour and seasoning.//
Gradually add milk.//
Bring to boil.//
Cook and stir for two minutes until thickened.//
Add turkey and carrots.//
Add broth.//
Cover and simmer for 15 minutes.//
Add peas.//
Cover and simmer for 15 minutes until vegetables are tender.